{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place coriander seeds and cumin seeds in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, toast <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add ginger, oil, garlic and lemon grass then grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then grind again <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add turmeric, curry powder, salt, sugar, and coconut milk then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl.","Place bowl with marinade on mixing bowl lid then weigh in pork. Stir well then cover with cling film and marinate in fridge for at least 6 hours or overnight.","Soak skewers in warm water for 30 minutes. Towards the end of soaking time, preheat grill to 230°C.","Thread marinated pork onto skewers (approx. 3 pieces per skewer).","Place skewers on grill tray lined with foil then grill for 15-20 minutes turning occasionally. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["¼ tsp coriander seeds","¼ tsp cumin seeds","5 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","20 g olive oil","4 garlic cloves","½ stick lemon grass, fresh, tough outer layer removed, cut in pieces (2 cm)","¼ tsp dried ground turmeric","½ tsp curry powder","1 tsp fine sea salt","1 Tbsp sugar","150 g coconut milk","680 g pork fillet, cut in large pieces (3 cm)"]}],"id":"r106622","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Z_fC66tLCNk\/XZQwwP0LCyI\/AAAAAAAAcok\/VjaU_hNzK3kcZP8oCRyJB9NEAwlJbqS_QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_eYZYLrq4lV3hBStB.png","title":"Grilled Pork Skewers with Turmeric","publishedAt":"2016-04-25T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"12.8 g","fat":"7.5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"2.1 g","calories":"532 kJ \/ 127 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, wooden skewers, aluminium foil, refrigerator, grill","basicInfo":["easy","10m","7h 10m","12 pieces"]}